19 Sec. 60. Chapter 427A of NRS is hereby amended by adding
20 thereto a new section to read as follows:
21 1. The Department, through the Division, shall conduct a
22 program to:
23 (a) Develop and carry out a public awareness campaign to
24 provide information to the public about the importance of
25 planning for long-term care that provides information relevant to
26 the changing demographics of this State. A public awareness
27 campaign carried out pursuant to this paragraph must engage
28 with various forms of media, including, without limitation,
29 television and digital platforms, to ensure the campaign reaches a
30 wide audience throughout this State.
31 (b) Create and maintain on the Internet website of the Division
32 comprehensive information on the resources and tools available to
33 residents of this State to assist residents of this State with planning
34 for long-term care.
35 (c) Coordinate with financial planners, providers of health
36 care, insurance companies and community organizations to
37 provide throughout this State workshops, seminars and
38 educational sessions that provide information on planning for
39 long-term care.
40 (d) Prepare planning guides, brochures and other printed
41 material and make such material available to the public,
42 community centers and other relevant organizations that may
43 distribute such materials to residents of this State. The materials
44 prepared and made available pursuant to this paragraph must
45 incorporate a range of educational material, including electronic
